      <center><h1>About Us</h1></center>
      <div class="container">
      <p>
        The University Hospital Pune (UHZ) is open to all patients every day and provides fundamental medical care and cutting-edge medicine in a central location in Pune. We use our superior academic knowledge to treat a wide range of health issues, taking a personal touch and utilizing highly specialized and up-to-date research.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-left">Broad and specialized range of services</h3>
      <p>
        Each year, we treat around 38,000 inpatients and 134,000 outpatients at our 43 departments and institutes. Our employees guarantee comprehensive and individualized medical support even beyond their specific disciplines. With 900 hospital beds and close to 300,000 inpatient days, UHZ is one of the largest hospitals in India.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-left">At the forefront of research</h3>
      <p>
        We research the latest treatment methods and apply them according to strict scientific criteria. We are the sole provider of many therapies in India. Patients with complex and multiple health problems travel from all over the country and abroad to be treated here. The percentage of patients with complex diseases is particularly high at the UHZ.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-left">Exceptional network</h3>
      <p>
        With regard to research and education, the UHZ is closely affiliated with the University of Pune's medical school and laboratories. We have numerous collaborative projects with ETH Pune. This puts the University Hospital Pune at the forefront of medical research in India and enjoys an excellent international reputation. Our professors travel worldwide to congresses in order to exchange experience and expertise.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-left">Team diversity</h3>
      <p>
        More than 8,500 employees from 86 countries work at the University Hospital Pune. They include 1,250 doctors, 2,500 highly trained nursing professionals and 800 medico-therapeutic and medico-technical employees. Approximately 2,000 employees conduct research and another 2,000 individuals provide non-medical support in areas such as finance, IT, facility management and catering. At the UHZ, a total of 120 occupations are represented by more than 500 roles.
      </p>
